The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: The cabinet committee on economic affairs today approved a proposal to sell shares of Maruti Udyog to all its 3,609 employees. Each employee will be offered 20 shares at a price of Rs 660 per share, sources said. The share sale to employees comes after the government sold 8 per cent equity in the carmaker last month for Rs Rs 1,567.60 crore. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: SpiceJet will convert options for 10 B-737 aircraft from Boeing into firm orders, besides securing options to buy 10 more planes in a deal worth $1.4 billion. Company officials declined to comment on the value of the deal.

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: DoT secretary Nripendra Mishra has emerged as the front runner for the top job in Trai. The cabinet secretariat is understood to have forwarded three names ? Nripendra Mishra, Raja Raman of the Tamil Nadu cadre and Manoranjan, secretary in the steel ministry. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 21: Ford India today introduced its Ikon Flair car model. Priced at Rs 4.69 lakh (ex-showroom Delhi), the new 1.3-litre Ikon Flair has a host of sporty features.

 Mumbai, Feb. 21: Sebi has advised the depositories to ask their depository participants to update their clients? bank details for refunds through electronic clearing system.




